# IDS (Intapp Design System)

This project uses the Intapp Design System (IDS/UDS). Use only IDS components, tokens, and icons — no third-party UI libraries or hardcoded values.

## Reference files

The full component reference for this project is at:
  `node_modules/@ids/react-next/claude/docs/using-uds-react-next.md`

Read this file when the user asks about UDS component props, slots, or behaviour, or when generating UDS component code.

Styles reference for this project is at:
  `node_modules/@ids/styles/claude/docs/using-uds-styles.md`

Read this file when the user asks about UDS design tokens as CSS custom properties, typography classes, theming via data-mode, or how to load the compiled CSS bundle. Also read it when generating SCSS or CSS that should use UDS tokens.

Tokens reference for this project is at:
  `node_modules/@ids/tokens/claude/docs/using-uds-tokens.md`

Read this file when the user asks about consuming raw design tokens directly (SCSS variables, JS exports, token JSON), token naming conventions, or using tokens outside of CSS.

The upgrade workflows for each `@ids/*` package are at:
  `node_modules/@ids/react-next/claude/skills/upgrade-ids-react-next/SKILL.md`
  `node_modules/@ids/styles/claude/skills/upgrade-ids-styles/SKILL.md`
  `node_modules/@ids/tokens/claude/skills/upgrade-ids-tokens/SKILL.md`

When the user says "upgrade @ids/&lt;pkg&gt;", "migrate to UDS vX", or has just bumped an `@ids/*` version in `package.json`, read the relevant skill file and follow its instructions.

## Imports

Import styles once in `app/layout.jsx`:

```js
import '@ids/react-next/styles.css';
import './globals.css'; // local overrides only
```

```jsx
'use client';
import dynamic from 'next/dynamic';

const UdsButton = dynamic(
  () => import('@ids/react-next/client').then((m) => ({ default: m.UdsButton })),
  { ssr: false }
);
```

Dark mode: add `data-mode="dark"` to `<html>` or `<body>`.

## Rules

1. **Never** call `import '@ids/react-next/client'` at the module level
2. **Never** use kebab-case tags like `<uds-button>` in JSX — use PascalCase like `<UdsButton>`
3. **Never** use `appearance` on buttons — use `variant`
4. **Never** put button text as inner HTML — use the `label` attribute
5. **Never** hardcode colors, spacing, or font sizes — use CSS custom properties from `@ids/tokens`
6. **Never** add the `ids-icon-` prefix to icon names — components add it automatically
7. **Always** add `'use client'` to any file that uses UDS components
8. **Always** give each component its own `dynamic()` call
9. **Always** import styles in `app/layout.jsx`, not in client components
10. **Always** use kebab-case for attribute values (e.g. `left-icon="add-circle"`)
11. **Always** use camelCase for React event handlers (`onClick`, `onChange`)
12. **Always** look up slot names from `node_modules/@ids/react-next/dist/src/components/stencil-generated/<ComponentName>/<ComponentName>.types.d.ts` before using them — guessed slot names silently drop content

## STRICT MODE (DES-1500)

- The PreToolUse hook (`.claude/hooks/check-ids.js`) blocks writes that violate IDS rules. Read its remediation feedback and re-apply the suggested fix.
- Never invent components or icons. Validate against `node_modules/@ids/react-next/manifest.json` and `node_modules/@ids-icons/assets/icons.json`.
- Use `var(--ids-*)` tokens for all colour and spacing. Never use hex/rgb literals or hardcoded `px`/`rem`/`em`.
- For component-pattern requests, follow `.cursor/rules/build-component-options.mdc` (generated at scaffold time).
- Override (`// ids-allow:`) is allowed but requires a user-confirmed reason.
